{#
  Embedded screen page — renders a Siti Agri screen inside an iframe.

  THIS IS THE KEY TEMPLATE demonstrating the embedded screen pattern.

  How the iframe works:
  1. The `src` attribute points to the SSO bridge URL (absolute URL,
     constructed server-side, pointing to the CAPD gateway origin)
  2. The browser requests the iframe content CROSS-ORIGIN from the CAPD
     gateway (localhost:3019) — a different origin from this page (localhost:3000)
  3. The CAPD gateway proxies the request to siti-agri-stub:3002
  4. The SSO bridge authenticates and renders the Siti Agri screen
  5. The screen appears within this page's iframe

  CROSS-ORIGIN SECURITY (all three must be configured):
  - Portal CSP frame-src must include the CAPD gateway origin:
    Content-Security-Policy: frame-src 'self' http://localhost:3019
    (configured via FRAME_SRC env var)
  - Siti Agri responses must include frame-ancestors for the CDP gateway:
    Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'self' http://localhost:3000
    (configured via SFD_PORTAL_ORIGIN env var in siti-agri-stub)
  - postMessage origin validated against the CAPD gateway origin (ssoBridgeOrigin),
    NOT window.location.origin (which is the CDP gateway — the wrong origin)
  - In production (HTTPS), cookies set by the iframe need SameSite=None; Secure

  PROGRESSIVE ENHANCEMENT:
  - Without JavaScript, the iframe still loads and displays content.
  - With JavaScript, the iframe auto-resizes to fit its content height
    (via postMessage from the embedded screen).
#}
{% extends "layout.njk" %}

{% from "govuk/components/back-link/macro.njk" import govukBackLink %}

{% block beforeContent %}
  {{ super() }}
  {{ govukBackLink({
    text: "Back to business overview",
    href: backLink
  }) }}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
      <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">{{ screenTitle }}</h1>

      {#
        The iframe container provides a styled wrapper with a minimum height.
        The .embedded-screen-frame class is defined in our SCSS and provides:
        - Full width of the content area
        - Minimum height so the page doesn't look empty while loading
        - A subtle border to visually separate portal content from iframe content
      #}
      <div class="embedded-screen-container" data-module="embedded-screen">
        {#
          IFRAME ATTRIBUTES:
          - src: The SSO bridge URL (same-origin via nginx gateway)
          - title: Accessibility — screen readers announce this
          - class: Styled to fill the container
          - data-origin: Used by JavaScript to validate postMessage origins

          SANDBOX (commented out for this demo):
          In production you might add sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin
          allow-forms allow-popups" to restrict the iframe content. However,
          this can break some Siti Agri screens that rely on parent frame access.
        #}
        <iframe
          src="{{ ssoBridgeUrl }}"
          title="{{ screenTitle }} - Siti Agri embedded screen"
          class="embedded-screen-frame"
          data-origin="{{ ssoBridgeOrigin }}"
        ></iframe>

        {#
          Loading overlay — shown while the iframe content loads.
          Hidden by JavaScript once the iframe fires its load event.
        #}
        <div class="embedded-screen-loading" aria-hidden="true">
          <p class="govuk-body">Loading...</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
